[2]
Date: Tue 27 May 2003
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: Minda News online, Sat 24 May 2003 [edited]
<http://www.mindanews.com/2003/05/24nws-dengue.html>

Philippines: Increased Number of Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever Cases on Mindanao
--------------------------------------------------
The Cotabato Regional and Medical Center (CRMC) here has recorded 41
additional dengue hemorrhagic fever cases in late May 2003. Early [in
May], it recorded 344 cases. Health authorities in South-central
Mindanao blamed the rainy season for the increase in the number of
mosquito-related diseases. Of the 41 new cases, 21 came from remote
and low-lying villages here, and the rest from nearby towns in North
Cotabato, Maguindanao, and Lanao del Sur.
Despite the rise, however, CRMC Chief Dr. Ariadne Silongan said there
is no cause for panic. "We already expected the number of dengue
cases to increase this rainy season but we do manage it very well,"
said Silongan in an interview over Catholic-run dxMS. The Department
of Health (DOH) in the region has monitored some 400 cases of dengue.
Only 5 deaths have been reported so far.
[Byline: Keith Bacongco]
